events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: — Payton Thorne played well in spurts, allowing No. 15 Michigan State to earn a lopsided win over Western Michigan despite struggling for long stretches of the opener on both sides of the ball.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 15 Michigan State sputters in 35-13 win over W. Michigan

Virginia Tech Hokies at Old Dominion Monarchs

headlines.description: — Blake Watson scored on a 1-yard run with 33 seconds to play and Old Dominion beat Virginia Tech for the second time in as many tries on its home field, 20-17 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Old Dominion does it again, beats Virginia Tech 20-17

headlines.description: — Darius Wilson passed for two touchdowns, Bronson Yoder rushed for 120 yards and a score, and FCS member William & Mary scored 21 unanswered points in the fourth quarter to beat FBS school Charlotte 41-24 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FCS member William & Mary gets first FBS win since 2009

events.name: Temple Owls at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: — Riley Leonard threw for two touchdowns and completed his first 15 passes of the season, boosting Duke to a 30-0 victory over Temple as coach Mike Elko won in his debut Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, defense spark Duke to 30-0 rout of Temple in opener

headlines.description: — Connor Bazelak wanted a fresh start at Indiana.

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: — Derius Davis scored on a 60-yard punt return and a 27-yard reverse to help TCU open the Sonny Dykes era with a 38-13 win over Colorado on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU cruises by Colorado 38-13 to kick off Sonny Dykes era
